:break-word;"><td class="cl-a338d4d3"><p class="cl-a338bdda"><span class="cl-a332909a">Phone</span></p></td><td class="cl-a338d4dc"><p class="cl-a338bdda"><span class="cl-a332909b">(512) 447-4141</span></p></td></tr><tr style="overflow-wrap:break-word;"><td class="cl-a338d4d3"><p class="cl-a338bdda"><span class="cl-a332909a">Website</span></p></td><td class="cl-a338d4dc"><p class="cl-a338bdda"><a href="http://www.integralcare.org/"><span class="cl-a332909b">http://www.integralcare.org/</span></a></p></td></tr><tr style="overflow-wrap:break-word;"><td class="cl-a338d4d3"><p class="cl-a338bdda"><span class="cl-a332909a">First Eligibility &amp; Referrals</span></p></td><td class="cl-a338d4dc"><p class="cl-a338bdda"><span class="cl-a332909b">PES is designated to serve any walk-in clients presenting in a psychiatric crisis. Clients who present with non-crisis needs will be provided with services or resource recommendations to meet their needs.</span></p></td></tr><tr style="overflow-wrap:break-word;"><td class="cl-a338d4d3"><p class="cl-a338bdda"><span class="cl-a332909a">Cost to Participant</span></p></td><td class="cl-a338d4dc"><p class="cl-a338bdda"><span class="cl-a332909b">Sliding scale</span></p></td></tr><tr style="overflow-wrap:break-word;"><td class="cl-a338d4d3"><p class="cl-a338bdda"><span class="cl-a332909a">Need Category</span></p></td><td class="cl-a338d4dc"><p class="cl-a338bdda"><span class="cl-a332909b">Behavioral Health Services</span></p></td></tr><tr style="overflow-wrap:break-word;"><td class="cl-a338d4d3"><p class="cl-a338bdda"><span class="cl-a332909a">Subcategory</span></p></td><td class="cl-a338d4dc"><p class="cl-a338bdda"><span class="cl-a332909b">Emergency</span></p></td></tr></tbody><tfoot><tr style="overflow-wrap:break-word;"><td  colspan="2"class="cl-a338d4dd"><p class="cl-a338bde4"><span class="cl-a332909c"></span></p></td></tr><tr style="overflow-wrap:break-word;"><td  colspan="2"class="cl-a338d4df"><p class="cl-a338bde4"><span class="cl-a